column1: Table 20. Supplemental data for 49 large city governments
Report title: Justice Expenditure and Employment Extracts 2011 Final, NCJ 250631
Data source: Justice Expenditure and Employment Extracts Program (JEEE)
Author: Jennifer Bronson, Ph.D., BJS Statistician
Table 20. Supplemental data for 49 large city governments
Note: Local government data are estimates subject to variability.
a/Population figures are from the Bureau of the Census, Annual Estimates of the Resident Population for the United States, regions, states, and Puerto Rico: April 1, 2010 to July 1, 2015 (May 2016).
b/"Total general expenditure" excludes utilities, county-operated liquor stores, and insurance trust benefits.
c/"General functions only" FTE excludes utilities and county-operated liquor stores.
